Upon checking the order 118028, we could see the customer selected service at checkout was not from our app. So, for such orders once they are imported to the app, the cheapest available service among the FedEx and USPS will be assigned automatically.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
For this order the cheapest available service was FedEx 2 Day with the cost $9.43 and it was automatically assigned for label generation.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The USPS service Priority Mail was also available for this order and its cost is $15.16. So, the FedEx service was assigned automatically for the label generation.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
FYI, the Stamps USPS PO Box rule is working fine.
&nbsp;
Best regards,
Sagar K S
